<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 2679/98 of 7 December 1998 on the functioning of the internal market in relation to the free movement of goods among the Member States </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2679/98 siseturu toimimise kohta liikmesriikidevahelise kaupade vaba liikumise osas 7. detsember 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 235 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 235, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas, as provided for in Article 7a of the Treaty, the internal market comprises an area without internal frontiers in which, in particular, the free movement of goods is ensured in accordance with Articles 30 to 36 of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) asutamislepingu artikli 7a kohaselt on siseturg sisepiirideta ala, kus koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artiklitega 30-36 tagatakse eelk&otilde;ige kaupade vaba liikumine; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas breaches of this principle, such as occur when in a given Member State the free movement of goods is obstructed by actions of private individuals, may cause grave disruption to the proper functioning of the internal market and inflict serious losses on the individuals affected; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tte rikkumine n&auml;iteks juhul, kui m&otilde;nes liikmesriigis takistab kaupade vaba liikumist &uuml;ksikisikute tegevus, v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada t&otilde;siseid h&auml;ireid siseturu n&otilde;uetekohases toimimises ning tuua asjaomastele isikutele m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rset kahju; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas, in order to ensure fulfilment of the obligations arising from the Treaty, and, in particular, to ensure the proper functioning of the internal market, Member States should, on the one hand, abstain from adopting measures or engaging in conduct liable to constitute an obstacle to trade and, on the other hand, take all necessary and proportionate measures with a view to facilitating the free movement of goods in their territory; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) asutamislepingust tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmise ning eelk&otilde;ige siseturu n&otilde;uetekohase toimimise tagamiseks peaksid liikmesriigid &uuml;helt poolt hoiduma meetmetest v&otilde;i tegevusest, mis v&otilde;iksid kujutada kaubanduse jaoks takistust, ning teiselt poolt v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud ja proportsionaalsed meetmed kaupade vaba liikumise h&otilde;lbustamiseks oma territooriumil; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas such measures must not affect the exercise of fundamental rights, including the right or freedom to strike; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) sellised meetmed ei tohi m&otilde;jutada p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste, sealhulgas streigi&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i -vabaduse teostamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas this Regulation does not prevent any actions which may be necessary in certain cases at Community level to respond to problems in the functioning of the internal market, taking into account, where appropriate, the application of this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus ei takista mis tahes meetmeid, mis v&otilde;ivad teatavatel juhtudel olla &uuml;henduse tasandil vajalikud siseturu toimimisel ilmnenud probleemide lahendamiseks, v&otilde;ttes v&otilde;imaluse korral arvesse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas Member States have exclusive competence as regards the maintenance of public order and the safeguarding of internal security as well as in determining whether, when and which measures are necessary and proportionate in order to facilitate the free movement of goods in their territory in a given situation; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) liikmesriikide ainup&auml;devuses on avaliku korra tagamine ja sisejulgeoleku kaitsmine, samuti selle &uuml;le otsustamine, kas, millal ja millised meetmed on konkreetsel juhul kaupade vaba liikumise h&otilde;lbustamiseks vajalikud ning proportsionaalsed; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas there should be adequate and rapid exchange of information between the Member States and the Commission on obstacles to the free movement of goods; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) liikmesriigid ja komisjon peaksid piisavalt ja kiirelt vahetama teavet kaupade vaba liikumise takistuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas a Member State on the territory of which obstacles to the free movement of goods occur should take all necessary and proportionate measures to restore as soon as possible the free movement of goods in their territory in order to avoid the risk that the disruption or loss in question will continue, increase or intensify and that there may be a breakdown in trade and in the contractual relations which underlie it; whereas such Member State should inform the Commission and, if requested, other Member States of the measures it has taken or intends to take in order fo fulfil this objective; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) liikmesriik, kelle territooriumil kaupade vaba liikumist takistatakse, peaks v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud ja proportsionaalsed meetmed kaupade vaba liikumise v&otilde;imalikult kiireks taastamiseks oma territooriumil, et v&auml;ltida k&otilde;nealuse h&auml;ire v&otilde;i kahju j&auml;tkumise, suurenemise v&otilde;i intensiivistumise riski ning kaubanduse ja selle aluseks olevate lepingusuhete katkemist; selline liikmesriik peaks teavitama komisjoni ning taotluse korral teisi liikmesriike meetmetest, mis on selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kavatsetakse v&otilde;tta; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the Commission, in fulfilment of its duty under the Treaty, should notify the Member State concerned of its view that a breach has occurred and the Member State should respond to that notification; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) komisjon peaks talle asutamislepinguga pandud kohustust t&auml;ites teatama asjaomasele liikmesriigile oma seisukoha, et toimunud on rikkumine, ning liikmesriik peaks nimetatud teatele vastama; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas the Treaty provides for no powers, other than those in Article 235 thereof, for the adoption of this Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> 10) asutamislepingus on k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmise volitused s&auml;testatud &uuml;ksnes artiklis 235, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Regulation: 1. the term 'obstacle' shall mean an obstacle to the free movement of goods among Member States which is attributable to a Member State, whether it involves action or inaction on its part, which may constitute a breach of Articles 30 to 36 of the Treaty and which: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: 1. "takistus" on liikmesriigi tegevusest v&otilde;i tegevusetusest tulenev liikmesriikidevahelise kaupade vaba liikumise takistus, millega v&otilde;idakse rikkuda asutamislepingu artikleid 30-36 ning mis: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) leads to serious disruption of the free movement of goods by physically or otherwise preventing, delaying or diverting their import into, export from or transport across a Member State, </inglise>
<eesti> a) p&otilde;hjustab t&otilde;sise h&auml;ire kaupade vabas liikumises, takistades, l&uuml;kates edasi v&otilde;i raskendades f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt v&otilde;i muul viisil nende importi liikmesriiki, eksporti liikmesriigist v&otilde;i vedu l&auml;bi liikmesriigi, </eesti>
<inglise> (b) causes serious loss to the individuals affected, and </inglise>
<eesti> b) p&otilde;hjustab asjaomastele isikutele olulist kahju, ja </eesti>
<inglise> (c) requires immediate action in order to prevent any continuation, increase or intensification of the disruption or loss in question; </inglise>
<eesti> c) n&otilde;uab viivitamatuid meetmeid k&otilde;nealuse h&auml;ire v&otilde;i kahju j&auml;tkumise, suurenemise v&otilde;i intensiivistumise v&auml;ltimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. the term 'inaction' shall cover the case when the competent authorities of a Member State, in the presence of an obstacle caused by actions taken by private individuals, fail to take all necessary and proportionate measures within their powers with a view to removing the obstacle and ensuring the free movement of goods in their territory. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. "tegevusetus" h&otilde;lmab juhtu, kus liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused ei v&otilde;ta eraisikute tegevuse kaudu p&otilde;hjustatud takistuse korral k&otilde;iki nende v&otilde;imuses olevaid vajalikke ja proportsionaalseid meetmeid takistuse k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja kaupade vaba liikumise tagamiseks oma territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation may not be interpreted as affecting in any way the exercise of fundamental rights as recognised in Member States, including the right or freedom to strike. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust ei tohi t&otilde;lgendada nii, nagu see takistaks mis tahes viisil liikmesriikides tunnustatud p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste, sealhulgas streigi&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i -vabaduse teostamist. </eesti>
<inglise> These rights may also include the right or freedom to take other actions covered by the specific industrial relations systems in Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud &otilde;iguste hulgas v&otilde;ib olla ka &otilde;igus v&otilde;i vabadus v&otilde;tta muid liikmesriikide t&ouml;&ouml;suhete eris&uuml;steemidega h&otilde;lmatud meetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When an obstacle occurs or when there is a threat thereof </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ilmneb takistus v&otilde;i tekib selle ilmnemise oht, </eesti>
<inglise> (a) any Member State (whether or not it is the Member State concerned) which has relevant information shall immediately transmit it to the Commission, and </inglise>
<eesti> a) edastab iga asjakohast teavet omav liikmesriik (kas asjaomane liikmesriik v&otilde;i mitte) selle viivitamatult komisjonile, ja </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the Commission shall immediately transmit to the Member States that information and any information from any other source which it may consider relevant. </inglise>
<eesti> b) komisjon edastab selle teabe ning mis tahes muust allikast saadud asjakohaseks peetava teabe viivitamatult liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State concerned shall respond as soon as possible to requests for information from the Commission and from other Member States concerning the nature of the obstacle or threat and the action which it has taken or proposes to take. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomane liikmesriik vastab komisjoni ja teiste liikmesriikide taotlustele saada teavet takistuse v&otilde;i selle ohu laadi ja v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kavandatavate meetmete kohta niipea kui v&otilde;imalik. </eesti>
<inglise> Information exchange between Member States shall also be transmitted to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikidevaheline teabevahetus edastatakse ka komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When an obstacle occurs, and subject to Article 2, the Member State concerned shall </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ilmneb takistus ja artiklist 2 ei tulene teisiti, peab asjaomane liikmesriik </eesti>
<inglise> (a) take all necessary and proportionate measures so that the free movement of goods is assured in the territory of the Member State in accordance with the Treaty, and </inglise>
<eesti> a) v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud ja proportsionaalsed meetmed, et tagada kaupade vaba liikumine liikmesriigi territooriumil vastavalt asutamislepingule, ja </eesti>
<inglise> (b) inform the Commission of the actions which its authorities have taken or intend to take. </inglise>
<eesti> b) teatama komisjonile oma asutuste poolt v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kavandatavatest meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall immediately transmit the information received under paragraph 1(b) to the other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon edastab l&otilde;ike 1 punkti b alusel saadud teabe viivitamata teistele liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the Commission considers that an obstacle is occurring in a Member State, it shall notify the Member State concerned of the reasons that have led the Commission to such a conclusion and shall request the Member State to take all necessary and proportionate measures to remove the said obstacle within a period which it shall determine with reference to the urgency of the case. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjon leiab, et liikmesriigis on ilmnenud takistus, teatab ta asjaomasele liikmesriigile p&otilde;hjused, mille alusel komisjon on j&otilde;udnud sellisele j&auml;reldusele ning taotleb liikmesriigilt k&otilde;ikide vajalike ja proportsionaalsete meetmete v&otilde;tmist nimetatud takistuse k&otilde;rvaldamiseks juhtumi kiireloomulisusest l&auml;htuvalt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajavahemiku jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In reaching its conclusion, the Commission shall have regard to Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;relduse tegemisel v&otilde;tab komisjon arvesse artiklit 2. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission may publish in the Official Journal of the European Communities the text of the notification which it has sent to the Member State concerned and shall immediately transmit the text to any party which requests it. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;ib asjaomasele liikmesriigile saadetud teatise avaldada Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas ning edastab teksti viivitamata k&otilde;ikidele pooltele, kes seda taotlevad. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State shall, within five working days of receipt of the text, either: </inglise>
<eesti> Viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast teksti k&auml;ttesaamist liikmesriik kas: </eesti>
<inglise> - inform the Commission of the steps which it has taken or intends to take to implement paragraph 1, or </inglise>
<eesti> - teatab komisjonile l&otilde;ike 1 rakendamiseks v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kavandatavad meetmed, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - communicate a reasoned submission as to why there is no obstacle constituting a breach of Articles 30 to 36 of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> - teeb teatavaks p&otilde;hjendatud selgituse selle kohta, miks asutamislepingu artikleid 30-36 rikkuvat takistust ei ole. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> In exceptional cases, the Commission may allow an extension of the deadline mentioned in paragraph 4 if the Member State submits a duly substantiated request and the grounds cited are deemed acceptable. </inglise>
<eesti> Erandjuhtudel v&otilde;ib komisjon lubada l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud t&auml;htaega pikendada, kui liikmesriik esitab n&otilde;uetekohaselt p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse ning osutatud p&otilde;hjused loetakse vastuv&otilde;etavateks. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
